-- Hungary Spends Half of Pension Assets, Vilaggazdasag Reports
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-08-16T06:14:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/hungary-spends-half-of-pension-assets-vilaggazdasag-reports.html
Hungarian private pension fund
assets, which the government nationalized last year, dropped to
591 billion forint ($2.6 billion) by the end of May, compared
with 3 trillion forint at the time the state acquired them,
 Vilaggazdasag  said, citing government data.  The Cabinet has spent about 1.5 trillion forint of the
assets buying back government debt and the value of the
remainder fell due to the economic crisis, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  